articles.text:
A Lagos State government representative was on Friday booed at the Experience, a programme l at the House of the Rock Cathedral, Lekki.

The atmosphere changed in the church when Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu’s representative was invited to speak to the crowd at the event.

The crowd started chanting and booed him from the beginning of his speech till the end.

This may be connected to the displeasure of Lagosians and youths concerning the End SARS Panel report.

Recall that Sanwo-Olu in the white paper released following End SARS panel report on Lekki toll gate shooting, said that not all the recommendations in the report would be accepted.

According to him, Lagos State Government accepts 11 out of the 32 recommendations made by the JPI in its report of 15th November 2021, rejected one (1) and accepted 6 (six) with modifications.

On the deaths recorded in the judicial panel report, the white-paper committee noted that the details in the document are not enough to conclude that the victims listed in the panel’s report were killed at the Lekki tollgate.

Here are some reactions from Nigerians after Sanwo-Olu’s representative was booed on stage:

@OfficialArole “ You booed someone in the presence of God. Abeg boo them more. Even Jesus flog for temple.”

@MsAdenike “I wish it was Babajide himself that came.”

@AbumeIfon “ Nigerians will never disappoint you, thank you to all the vices who screamed their displeasure tonight. Pastor Paul no worry even God asked us not to sit in the seat of the scornful.”

@Islimfit “ The people at #TheExperience2021 switched from Jesu to esu. Most definitely the highlight of the event. Imagine if it was Sanwo Olu that came himself. “

@SavyRinu “ Mr Gov. thinks this generation is a joke? Sanwo-Olu, sorosoke! Who ordered the shootings?

@WinieIguwa “ Pastor Paul said the Behavior was unscriptural. Pastor, the way this government has treated us is unbiblical and unscriptural too.

We shall pray for our leaders but Omo, people are tired.”

@Barnie “ They are booing Sanwolu as his aide represents him at the #TheExperience2021. The booing even got louder when he is quoting a scripture! Fantastic, the people are not happy with Lagos state leadership and the handwriting is clear!”

@CitizenOla “I love the attitude of Nigerians against Sanwo-Olu and his representative in the ongoing #TheExperience2021. It’s why the murderer won’t show up at the event in person.We must keep bullying these vagabonds in power until sense is restored to our leadership roles.”

@Tochukwu “ It would have been worse, if the governor came himself.Sorry Pastor Paul,but the people are tired.”

